page.title: 03HUMBER ESTUARY-COMMERCIAL
page.content: { HUMBER RIVER}The River Humber is busy with many ships going to Hull, Goole, River Trent Quays Grimsby and Immingham.Hers are some of them. { OIL TANKERS}bring oil products from abroad to Immingham Dock and Saltend. { ORE CARRIERS}bring iron ore and other bulk cargoes to Immingham for use at British Steel,Scunthorpe { FERRIES}Roll on Roll off go to Rotterdam,Zeebrugge,Immingham,the continent,and Scandinavia. {STERN TRAWLERS}fish out of Grimsby and Hull. They mostly fish off Norway. {SEINE NET FISHING VESSELS} based at Grimsby,fish mainly in the North Sea. {DANISH BUTTER BOAT}A regular to Grimsby,brings butter and Bacon from Denmark. {COASTERS and GENERAL CARGO VESSELS travel to the Humber from all parts.
